access to information

58:00.711 --> 58:02.945
is necessary to run a business.

58:03.047 --> 58:05.347
- When your own employee
turns you in to the FBI,

58:06.584 --> 58:09.284
you're gonna take a
few more precautions.

58:09.386 --> 58:10.619
- If you're not
doing anything wrong,

58:10.721 --> 58:12.721
you got nothing to hide.

58:12.823 --> 58:15.057
- Spoken like a true cop.

58:16.160 --> 58:18.093
And he was never charged.

58:18.195 --> 58:20.162
- Doesn't mean he didn't do it.

58:20.264 --> 58:23.165
- Look, he hid some
things from me,

58:23.267 --> 58:25.067
and he got involved
with the wrong people,

58:25.169 --> 58:29.071
but I don't think he set
out to do anything wrong.

58:29.173 --> 58:30.639
- Okay.

58:30.741 --> 58:32.474
- Steve, there's no way.

58:32.576 --> 58:33.909
- Wait.

58:34.011 --> 58:35.677
What are these deposits from?

58:35.779 --> 58:37.412
- It's payments from
apartment buildings

58:37.515 --> 58:39.081
we manage in New York.

58:39.183 --> 58:41.083
- I thought you guys
just developed property.

58:41.185 --> 58:42.150
- I convinced Brent
that we needed

58:42.253 --> 58:43.752
more dependable
streams of income

58:43.854 --> 58:46.288
in case our development
deals failed.

58:46.390 --> 58:48.423
- Okay, very practical.

58:48.526 --> 58:49.791
Looks like a good decision too.

58:49.894 --> 58:51.260
